---
const misreads = [
  { bold: 'A reporting problem', rest: 'mistaken for a CRM problem.' },
  { bold: 'An operational problem', rest: 'mistaken for an AI problem.' },
  { bold: 'A business that has adapted', rest: 'to the limits of its software, instead of the reverse.' },
];
const decisions = ['Stay', 'Change', 'Automate', 'Buy', 'Build'];
---

<section class="section case" id="the-case">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="case__head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">The Case for a Review</p>
      <h2>Most organizations don't have<br />a technology problem.</h2>
      <p class="case__intro">
        Every week brings another AI announcement, another platform, another consultant explaining why you
        need digital transformation. Most organizations respond by asking: <em>"What software should we
        implement?"</em> That's the wrong question.
      </p>
      <p class="case__intro">
        In 30 years across global telecoms, growing technology firms and non-profits, the same pattern
        repeats regardless of size or industry: they have a <strong>business problem</strong> they're trying
        to solve with technology.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ul class="case__list reveal">
      {misreads.map((m) => (
        <li>
          <span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span><strong>{m.bold}</strong> {m.rest}</span>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>

    <blockquote class="case__quote reveal">
      <p>Solve the wrong problem and better software simply gets you to the wrong destination faster.</p>
      <cite>The Central Question</cite>
    </blockquote>

    <div class="case__decisions reveal">
      <p class="case__decisions-lead">
        The review steps back from technology to understand how the business should operate. Only then do
        the technology decisions get made:
      </p>
      <div class="chips">
        {decisions.map((d) => <span class="chip">{d}</span>)}
      </div>
      <p class="case__punch">
        And most importantly: <span>what shouldn't be built at all?</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .case__head { max-width: 62ch; }
  .case h2 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.25rem); margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
  .case__intro { font-size: 1.12rem; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; max-width: 64ch; }
  .case__intro em { color: var(--text); font-style: italic; }
  .case__intro strong { color: var(--text); }

  .case__list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 3.5rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.1rem;
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .case__list li { display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: baseline; font-size: 1.1rem; }
  .case__list .dot {
    flex: none;
    width: 10px; height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--coral);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  .case__list strong { color: var(--text); }
  .case__list li { color: var(--text-muted); }

  .case__quote {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--text-on-dark);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    text-align: center;
    margin: 0 0 3.5rem;
  }
  .case__quote p {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3.6vw, 2.1rem);
    line-height: 1.25;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    max-width: 22ch;
    margin: 0 auto 1.25rem;
  }
  .case__quote cite {
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal-bright);
  }

  .case__decisions { text-align: center; max-width: 720px; margin-inline: auto; }
  .case__decisions-lead { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
  .chips {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }
  .chip {
    background: var(--paper-2);
    color: var(--teal);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.7rem 1.4rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
  .case__punch { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .case__punch span { color: var(--coral); font-weight: 700; font-family: var(--font-display); }
</style>
